'''Sveta Gora''' ({{IPA-sl|ˈsʋeːta ˈɡɔːɾa|pron}}; {{lang-it|Monte Santo di Gorizia}}) is a settlement in western [[Slovenia]] in the Municipality of [[Nova Gorica]].<ref>[http://www.nova-gorica.si/ Nova Gorica municipal site]</ref> It encompasses Holy Mount ({{lang-sl|Sveta gora}}), above the [[Soča]] Valley and southwest of the [[Banjšice Plateau]].

==History==
{{multiple image
 | align = left
 | footer = World War One bunkers
 | footer_align = center
 | image1 = Sveta Gora Slovenia - bunker 2.jpg
 | width1 = 202
 | caption1 = Bunker exterior
 | image2 = Sveta Gora Slovenia - bunker 3 interior.jpg
 | width2 = 200
 | caption2 = Bunker interior
}}
In May 1917 Sveta Gora was the scene of heavy fighting between [[Austria-Hungary|Austrian]] and [[Italy|Italian]] forces.{{cn|date=September 2016}} Several Austro-Hungarian bunkers are found along Skalnica Road (''Skalniška cesta'') leading to the Franciscan monastery and church at the top of Mount Skalnica ({{convert|681|m|sp=us|disp=or}}). Sveta Gora became an independent settlement in 2006, when its territory was administratively separated from the territory of [[Solkan]] and [[Grgar]].<ref name="SURS"/>
